==English==

===Adverb===
'''crescendo'''

===Etymology===
Borrowed from Italian ''crescendo'', present participle of ''crescere'', meaning "to grow" or "to increase."

===Meanings===

#''Music.'' The musical term meaning that the volume of the notes gradually gets louder.  Abbreviation: cresc.
#A dynamic sign, shaped like an angle with the pointer on the left, to indicate that the volume gets gradually louder.

